# Feature Requirements Template
#
# Fill in this template with your feature idea. You can:
# 1. Use this template and push to GitHub (triggers automatically)
# 2. Copy to a new .gherkin file in features/ directory
# 3. Create a GitHub issue and paste the content (add 'auto-implement' label)
# 4. Use with CLI: python feature_controller.py --requirements-file features/TEMPLATE.gherkin
#
# Tips:
# - Be specific about user actions and expected outcomes
# - Include edge cases and error scenarios
# - One feature per file works best
# - Multiple scenarios are encouraged
# - Use "Given/When/Then" format for clarity

Feature: [Feature Name - Short, descriptive title]
  As a [type of user]
  I want to [goal/desire]
  So that [benefit/value]

  # Background (optional): Common setup for all scenarios
  Background:
    Given [common precondition that applies to all scenarios]
    And [another common precondition]

  # Scenario 1: Happy path - the main success scenario
  Scenario: [Descriptive scenario name - what succeeds]
    Given [precondition - the starting state]
    And [another precondition if needed]
    When [action - what the user does]
    And [another action if needed]
    Then [expected outcome - what should happen]
    And [another expected outcome]

  # Scenario 2: Alternative path or edge case
  Scenario: [Another scenario - edge case or alternative]
    Given [different starting state]
    When [different action]
    Then [different expected outcome]

  # Scenario 3: Error case - what happens when things go wrong
  Scenario: [Error scenario - what fails gracefully]
    Given [precondition that leads to error]
    When [action that triggers error]
    Then [error handling - how system responds]
    And [user feedback - what user sees]

  # Add more scenarios as needed to cover:
  # - Different user types
  # - Edge cases
  # - Error conditions
  # - Security considerations
  # - Performance requirements


