# Feature: User Authentication
#   As a user
#   I want to log in securely with my email and password
#   So that I can access my personalized dashboard
#
#   Background:
#     Given the application is running
#     And the database is accessible
#
#   Scenario: Successful login with valid credentials
#     Given a user exists with email "user@example.com" and password "SecurePass123"
#     And the user is not currently logged in
#     When the user enters email "user@example.com"
#     And the user enters password "SecurePass123"
#     And the user clicks the "Log In" button
#     Then the user should be redirected to "/dashboard"
#     And the user should see a welcome message "Welcome back!"
#     And a session token should be created
#
#   Scenario: Failed login with incorrect password
#     Given a user exists with email "user@example.com"
#     When the user enters email "user@example.com"
#     And the user enters password "WrongPassword"
#     And the user clicks the "Log In" button
#     Then the user should remain on the login page
#     And an error message should display "Invalid email or password"
#     And no session token should be created
#
#   Scenario: Failed login with non-existent email
#     Given no user exists with email "nobody@example.com"
#     When the user enters email "nobody@example.com"
#     And the user enters password "AnyPassword"
#     And the user clicks the "Log In" button
#     Then the user should remain on the login page
#     And an error message should display "Invalid email or password"
#     And the error should not reveal whether the email exists
#
#   Scenario: Account lockout after multiple failed attempts
#     Given a user exists with email "user@example.com"
#     And the user has failed to log in 4 times in the last 10 minutes
#     When the user enters email "user@example.com"
#     And the user enters password "WrongPassword"
#     And the user clicks the "Log In" button
#     Then the user should see an error "Account temporarily locked. Try again in 15 minutes."
#     And the account should be locked for 15 minutes
#     And a notification email should be sent to "user@example.com"


# ==============================================================================
# QUICK REFERENCE: Gherkin Keywords
# ==============================================================================
#
# Feature: High-level description of a software feature
# Background: Common steps that run before each scenario
# Scenario: Specific example/test case
# Given: Preconditions (initial context/state)
# When: Action/event that triggers behavior
# Then: Expected outcome/result
# And: Additional step (same type as previous)
# But: Negative assertion (alternative to And)
# Scenario Outline: Template for multiple scenarios with examples
# Examples: Data table for Scenario Outline
#
# ==============================================================================
# BEST PRACTICES
# ==============================================================================
#
# ✓ DO:
# - Write from the user's perspective
# - Be specific and concrete
# - Include positive and negative scenarios
# - Focus on behavior, not implementation
# - Use present tense
# - One action per When step when possible
#
# ✗ DON'T:
# - Use technical jargon unnecessarily
# - Describe UI implementation details
# - Make scenarios too long (split into multiple)
# - Assume knowledge - be explicit
# - Write vague expectations
